    "problemStatement": "You love array, don't you?\n\nYou are given two integer NNN and MMM, along with an array BBB of length NNN containing **pairwise distinct** integers. You have to find the number of array AAA of length NNN satisfying the follow conditions:\n\n\n1\u2264Ai\u2264M1 \\leq A_i \\leq M1\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264M.\nAi\u2260AjA_i \\neq A_jAi\u200b\ue020=Aj\u200b for all 1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N1 \\le i \\lt j \\le N1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N.\nAi\u2260BiA_i \\neq B_iAi\u200b\ue020=Bi\u200b for all 1\u2264i\u2264N1 \\le i \\le N1\u2264i\u2264N.\nSince the answer can be very large, output it under modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of the input contains two space-separated integers NNN and MMM.\nThe second line of the input contains NNN separated integers B1,B2,\u2026,BNB_1, B_2, \\dots, B_NB1\u200b,B2\u200b,\u2026,BN\u200b - the array BBB.\n\n\nOutput Format\nOutput on a single line the number of satisfactory array modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264N\u22642\u22c51051 \\leq N \\leq 2 \\cdot 10^51\u2264N\u22642\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264M\u22643\u22c51051 \\leq M \\leq 3 \\cdot 10^51\u2264M\u22643\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264Bi\u22641091 \\leq B_i \\leq 10^91\u2264Bi\u200b\u2264109",
      "Bi\u2260BjB_i \\neq B_jBi\u200b\ue020=Bj\u200b for all 1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N1 \\le i \\lt j \\le N1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N."
    ],
